The paper proposes a method for automated detection of lymph node metastasis and pN-stage prediction in breast cancer using convolutional neural networks (CNN). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of CNNs for image analysis and classification also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the difficulty in handling gigapixel images, which could be relevant to the deep learning (cs.DL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques for slide-level classification, which could be relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
